		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2024 SI"></a><br><code>sle2024s/paper10</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2024 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Grammar-based test suite construction using coverage-directed algorithms over LR-graphs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ChristoffRossouw.html">Christoff Rossouw</a>, <a href="../profile/BerndFischer.html">Bernd Fischer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jss.2024.112068">10.1016/j.jss.2024.112068</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2020/paper04.html"><em>Test Case Generation from Context-Free Grammars using Generalized Traversal of LR-automata</em></a> (SLE 2020)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagM">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is an algorithm for generating grammar-based test suites that satisfy coverage criteria via LR-automaton graph exploration.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It relies on analysis of grammar-derived LR automata/graphs (push/pop edges, conflicts) to guide construction of valid derivations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> The paper empirically evaluates efficiency/effectiveness (including comparisons to prior LR-graph exploration approaches).
</li></ul></li></ul>
